abstract: Several candidates criticized Senator Elizabeth Warren’s health care proposal and backed proposals to impose big taxes on the wealthy.
snippet: Several candidates criticized Senator Elizabeth Warren’s health care proposal and backed proposals to impose big taxes on the wealthy.
lead_paragraph: Good Wednesday. This year’s DealBook Summit will feature speakers like Bill Gates, Hillary Clinton, Ginni Rometty of IBM and Makan Delrahim, the head of the Justice Department’s antitrust division. Apply to attend here. (Sign up here to get this in your inbox each morning.)

headline_main: It Was the Best of Warren. It Was the Worst of Warren.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren fielded all the attacks that being a front-runner brings, and Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar made their cases as moderate alternatives.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren fielded all the attacks that being a front-runner brings, and Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar made their cases as moderate alternatives.
lead_paragraph: Twitter can’t tell us whether, or how, Tuesday’s CNN/New York Times debate might change voters’ minds. But it can give us the perspectives of some of the people with expertise on primary races: veteran campaign strategists and consultants from both parties.

headline_main: Who Won the Debate? Experts Weigh In

abstract: Shifts added or subtracted at short notice play havoc with budgets and lives, and disproportionately hurt black and Hispanic women.
snippet: Shifts added or subtracted at short notice play havoc with budgets and lives, and disproportionately hurt black and Hispanic women.
lead_paragraph: Unpredictable schedules can be brutal for hourly workers, upending their lives. New research shows that African-Americans, Hispanics and other minorities — particularly women — are much more likely to be assigned irregular schedules, and that the harmful repercussions are felt not just by the workers but also their families.

abstract: The Midwestern centrists are the only two plausible not-Biden candidates.
snippet: The Midwestern centrists are the only two plausible not-Biden candidates.
lead_paragraph: The ridiculous number of candidates on the Democratic stage last night created a fundamentally misleading aural and visual impression. Watching without access to polling data, you might have imagined that this was some sort of wild careening mess of a primary race, when really it’s remarkably consolidated.
